# Component Authoring Standards

## Scope
Apply these rules to every file matching:
- `src/components/**/*.jsx`
- `src/pages/**/*.jsx`
- `src/layouts/**/*.jsx`

---

## Standard File Structure

Every component file must follow this import order:

```jsx
// 1. React imports first
import { useState } from 'react';

// 2. Third-party library imports
import { Link } from 'react-router-dom';

// 3. Internal component imports — always use @/ alias
import SectionHeader from '@/components/ui/SectionHeader';
import GetInTouchForm from '@/components/ui/GetInTouchForm';

// 4. Data imports
import { products } from '@/data/products';

// 5. Named export for all shared/UI components
export function ExampleCard({ title, description, image }) {
  return (
    <div className="...">
      {/* JSX here */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

## Page Component Template

```jsx
// src/pages/PageName/PageName.jsx
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout';
import SectionHeader from '@/components/ui/SectionHeader';
import GetInTouchForm from '@/components/ui/GetInTouchForm';
import { HeroSection } from './components/HeroSection';
import { ContentSection } from './components/ContentSection';

export default function PageName() {
  return (
    <MainLayout>
      <HeroSection />
      <ContentSection />
      <GetInTouchForm />
    </MainLayout>
  );
}
```

---

## index.js Pattern

Every page folder must have an `index.js` re-export:

```js
// src/pages/PageName/index.js
export { default } from './PageName';
```

---

## Tailwind CSS Rules

- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively
- No inline `style={{}}` — except for truly dynamic values that Tailwind cannot express
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Use design token classes from `tailwind.config.js` (e.g. `text-navy`, `bg-primary-blue`)
- Never use arbitrary pixel values like `w-[347px]` for layout — use spacing scale
- Arbitrary values are acceptable only for specific image dimensions

---

## Props

- Destructure at the function signature: `function Card({ title, image, href })`
- Provide defaults for optional props: `function Card({ align = 'center' })`
- Never hardcode content strings — they must come from props or `src/data/`
- All site config (phone, email, address, socials) → import from `src/config/siteConfig.js`

---

## Import Alias

Always use `@/` for any cross-folder import. Never use deep relative paths.

```jsx
// ✅ Correct
import SectionHeader from '@/components/ui/SectionHeader';
import { products } from '@/data/products';
import { ROUTES } from '@/config/routes';

// ❌ Wrong
import SectionHeader from '../../../components/ui/SectionHeader';
```

---

## Hard Rules — Never Break These

| Rule | Wrong | Correct |
|---|---|---|
| HTML class attribute | `class="..."` | `className="..."` |
| TypeScript syntax | `interface Props`, `: string` | Plain JS only |
| Per-component CSS | `import './Card.css'` | Tailwind classes only |
| React function type | `React.FC` | Plain function |
| Shared component export | `export default SectionHeader` | `export function SectionHeader` |
| Page component export | `export function HomePage` | `export default function HomePage` |
